1. Guide suggest we use ActiveQuery
https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/blob/master/docs/guide/db-active-record.md
> Tip: In big projects, it is recommended that you use customized query classes to hold most query-related code so that the Active Record classes can be kept clean.

Every time I write, I need to consider adding a table prefix.
Otherwise, there will be an error when joinWith because there is no table prefix
Example:
```php
class Table1Query extend \yii\db\ActiveQuery
{
    public function init()
    {
        $this->active();
    }
    public function active()
    {
        return $this->andWhere(['table1.active' => 1]);
    }
}
```
Search Model
```php

    public function search($params)
    {
        $query = Table2::find()->alias('table2');
        $query->innerJoinWith(['table1']);

        // add conditions that should always apply here

        $dataProvider = new ActiveDataProvider([
            'query' => $query,
            'sort' => ['defaultOrder' => ['id' => SORT_DESC]]
        ]);
        
        $dataProvider->sort->attributes['table1_name'] = [
            'asc' => ['table1.name' => SORT_ASC],
            'desc' => ['table1.name' => SORT_DESC],
        ];

        $this->load($params);

        // grid filtering conditions
        $query->andFilterWhere([
            'table2.id' => $this->id,
        ]);

        $query->andFilterWhere(['like', 'table1.name', $this->table1_name])
    }
```
It's very cumbersome to write this every time, especially when the project is just beginning to develop.

**I try to use this solution**
```php
class Table1Query extend \yii\db\ActiveQuery
{
    public $prefix = 'table1';
    
    public function init()
    {
        $this->from([$this->prefix => \app\models\Table1::tableName()]);
        $this->active();
    }

    public function prefix($column)
    {
        return $this->prefix ? $this->prefix . '.' . $column : $column;
    }
    public function active()
    {
        return $this->andWhere([$this->prefix('active') => 1]);
    }
}
```
Search Model
```php

    public function search($params)
    {
        $query = Table2::find()
        $query->innerJoinWith(['table1']);

        // add conditions that should always apply here

        $dataProvider = new ActiveDataProvider([
            'query' => $query,
            'sort' => ['defaultOrder' => ['id' => SORT_DESC]]
        ]);
        
        $dataProvider->sort->attributes['table1_name'] = [
            'asc' => [$this->getTable1()->prefix('name') => SORT_ASC],
            'desc' => [$this->getTable1()->prefix('name') => SORT_DESC],
        ];

        $this->load($params);

        // grid filtering conditions
        $query->andFilterWhere([
            $query->prefix('id') => $this->id,
        ]);

        $query->andFilterWhere(['like', $this->getTable1()->prefix('name'), $this->table1_name])
    }
```
After trying, I think maybe it can be implemented inside `\yii\db\ActiveQuery`
or 
In `where` and `onCondition`  According to from conversion  
> If there is only one table, add no prefix (or all add table prefix)  
> If there is no `from` or `alias`, use `tableName` as the prefix. Use `from` or `alias` if it exists

**There may be many problems or use other better ways**

